<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="219" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,355,1679]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1615,1642]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet is derived from the Japanese name for a devil or demon. This is in reference to the male horns, which are similar to those in popular portrayals of demons. It is feminine.
</paragraph>
